xplored from perspectives such as ecocriticism and postcolonialism. The book will be of interest to researchers and post- and- undergraduate students in various fields within the Humanities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aGothic 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Modern / 21st Century .2bisacsh  aGothic crime.  aGothic humour.  aNordic Gothic fiction.  aNordic folklore.  aNordic welfare systems.  aecocriticism.  ageriatric Gothic.  anew media.  apostcolonialism.  atroll Gothic.1 aHõglund, Johan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHöglund, Johan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeffler, Yvonne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeffler, Yvonne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTroy, Maria Holmgren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTroy, Maria Holmgren, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWijkmark, Sofia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWijkmark, Sofia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612644340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526126443423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526126443/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles